&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting to: Chief Operating Officer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(78, 167, 46);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About This Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Head of Finance is charged with overseeing the financial strategy and management of the financial organization of this indirect, wholly-owned subsidiary of Italfarmaco, SpA.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;This person serves as a strategic business partner to the President, Board, COO, and leadership team and maintains responsibility for all corporate financial functions, including accounting, AP, Order-to-cash, audit, treasury, investments, financial operations, planning &amp;amp; forecasting, risk management, and tax.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;They will also be the primary point of contact and collaboration with ITF Group Central Finance function. The Head of Finance is a highly collaborative member of the ITF team, outward looking, strategically engaged, market sensitive and attuned to the urgency, pace and energy of the Company as it commercializes its rare disease drug.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is responsible for compliance with both statutory and management reporting obligations ensuring that ITF maintains the highest level of ethics, profitability, financial strength and operating efficiency as the Company deepens the launch of this critically important medicine.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(78, 167, 46);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee all aspects of financial planning and reporting, including the controller function, accounting, treasury, tax strategy and compliance, and external tax advisors, to ensure compliance with financial reporting standards,&amp;nbsp;shareholder&amp;nbsp;and ITF Group requirements, as well as statutory and legal requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead monthly close, forecasting, and annual planning activities, including headcount, operating expenses, and capital investments, by working closely with internal and external partners to support strategic planning and operational decision-making.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the budgeting process, including developing, communicating, and driving budget timelines; creating an efficient and effective review structure with leadership; creating budget templates; creating and&amp;nbsp;maintaining&amp;nbsp;budget roll-up files; and preparing budget deliverables for the Executive Leadership Team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop policies and programs to reflect the desired standard of performance for the finance function, using both internal staff and external consultants, as&amp;nbsp;appropriate.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain ITF’s insurance policies and risk management program.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead all treasury activities, including building and&amp;nbsp;maintaining&amp;nbsp;banking relationships.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the liaison to key vendors, including financial institutions, external tax and financial accountants, auditors, and attorneys, as&amp;nbsp;appropriate.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee cash flow planning and manage cash management goals for the organization.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain ITF’s investment policy and strategy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve ITF’s accounting operations, including AP, Treasury, Expense Reports, and Payroll.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Market Access and external parties to understand ITF’s returns, rebates, copay liabilities, government pricing requirements, HCP transparency reporting, and other gross-to-net sales adjustments to ensure complete and&amp;nbsp;accurate&amp;nbsp;accruals and reporting.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with legal, European colleagues, and external parties to ensure&amp;nbsp;timely&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;accurate&amp;nbsp

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 48, 87);&quot;&gt;Reports To: MSL Team Lead, Head of US Field Medical&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(14, 141, 57);&quot;&gt;About This Role:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Medical Science Liaison (MSL) is a field-facing role focused on developing and maintaining professional clinical/scientific relationships with external medical experts including pediatric neurologists, neuromuscular specialists, and neurologists, who are involved in the treatment of Duchenne muscular dystrophy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the clinical and medical expert on the company’s products and therapeutic areas, our MSLs build long-term relationships and establish rapport with clinicians in hospitals, clinics, and academic centers through highly scientific product and disease state discussions that support the safe and effective utilization of ITF’s therapies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position will play a key role in supporting ITF’s medical affairs goals by contributing to internal initiatives such as ad boards, speaker training, and clinical insights projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate brings a strong foundation in rare neuromuscular diseases, with a preference for prior experience in DMD. Comfort navigating complex scientific conversations, working autonomously in the field, and contributing to a collaborative and close-knit medical affairs team is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role supports care centers in KS, MO, NE, IA, SD, ND, MN, WI, and IL&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(14, 141, 57);&quot;&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong, trust‑based relationships with pediatric neurologists, neuromuscular specialists, and other key medical experts at major care centers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage in scientific exchange with healthcare professionals around clinical and research data, while capturing field insights to drive the evolution of strategic plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver fair-balanced and objective clinical and scientific presentations to healthcare professionals (HCPs), payors, and patient organizations in response to unsolicited requests for information on the use of company products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a core liaison to key institutions, supporting ongoing and future clinical studies and scientific collaborations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend national and regional medical meetings and symposia to engage in discussion and cultivate professional relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with external medical experts on medical affairs initiatives, including publications, medical education opportunities, and training as appropriate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the preparation and execution of scientific materials for marketed and pipeline assets, including delivering compelling presentations, assisting with slide preparation/review, and facilitating interactive discussion groups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(14, 141, 57);&quot;&gt;Who You Are:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are an experienced professional with a passion for building and sustaining trusted clinical and scientific relationships with external medical experts. You have a strong track record of designing and delivering engaging, informative training programs that keep teams aligned with the latest medical insights and industry best practices. You bring an analytical mindset and excellent problem-solving skills, allowing you to adapt quickly to changing priorities and deadlines. With a solid understanding of the pharmaceutical delivery process, you consistently operate in a compliant and ethical manner within a highly regulated industry.&lt;/p&gt;
